==历史==
第四大道线最早为纽约市“双重合约”地铁建设规划的一部分，该线替换了旧有的{{link-en|第五大道线 (布鲁克林高架铁路)|Fifth Avenue Line (Brooklyn elevated)|第五大道线高架铁路}}。<ref name="NYTimes-BMT4Av-86StExt-Feb1912">{{cite web|title=Brooklyn Subway Extension Plan: Fourth Ave. Line to 86th St., Tunnel to Staten Island, and Eventually a Through Route to Coney Island|url=https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1912/02/16/104891453.pdf|website=[[The_New_York_Times|nytimes.com]]|publisher=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|accessdate=2015-06-28|date=1912-02-16|archive-date=2021-06-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210603090423/https://timesmachine.nytimes.com/timesmachine/1912/02/16/104891453.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

该线首段起于[[德卡尔布大道车站_(BMT第四大道线)|德卡尔布大道车站]]，终于[[36街车站_(BMT第四大道线)|36街车站]]，于1909年11月开建。<ref name="NYTImes-BMT4Av-DirtFly-1909">{{cite web|title=Fourth Ave. Subway Dirt Begins to Fly|url=https://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive-free/pdf?res=9903E7DE1539E733A25757C1A9679D946897D6CF|website=[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]|publisher=[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]|accessdate=2017-04-21|date=1909-01-14|archive-date=2017-04-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170422123111/https://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive-free/pdf?res=9903E7DE1539E733A25757C1A9679D946897D6CF|dead-url=no}}</ref>而该线最南的一段（[[86街车站_(BMT第四大道线)|86街车站]]）则于1912年10月开建。<ref name="NYTimes-BMT4Av-86StExt-Feb1912" /><ref name="NYTimes-4AvExtGroundbrk-1912">{{cite web|title=Bay Ridge Turns Out For Start of Subway|url=https://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive-free/pdf?res=9401E2D91F3CE633A25754C2A9669D946396D6CF|website=[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]|publisher=[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]|accessdate=2017-04-21|date=1912-10-27|archive-date=2017-04-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170422035141/https://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive-free/pdf?res=9401E2D91F3CE633A25754C2A9669D946396D6CF|dead-url=no}}</ref>该线的部分支线（包括从[[36街车站_(BMT第四大道线)|36街车站]]以南分离的[[BMT西城线|BMT西城线]]，以及从[[59街车站_(BMT第四大道线)|59街车站]]以南延伸出的[[BMT海滩线|BMT海滩线]]）也开始建设，以取代旧有的路面铁路。<ref name="NYTimes-BMT4Av-86StExt-Feb1912" />该线开建后，第四大道沿线有多个房地产项目开建。<ref name="NYTimes-4AvOpening-1915">{{cite web|title=Two Subway Branches Open Up New Era of Prosperity for Brooklyn and Queens|url=https://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive-free/pdf?res=9E0DEFD71631E733A05754C2A9609C946496D6CF|website=[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]|publisher=[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]|accessdate=2017-04-21|date=1915-06-27|archive-date=2017-04-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170422034620/https://query.nytimes.com/mem/archive-free/pdf?res=9E0DEFD71631E733A05754C2A9609C946496D6CF|dead-url=no}}</ref>

